# .leak-patterns — copy this file to ../.leak-patterns and edit.
#
# One regex per line. Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines OK.
# These patterns are personal/sensitive — the file containing them is
# gitignored. Never commit a populated .leak-patterns.
#
# The check-leaks.sh script will fail if ANY of these patterns appear in
# committed source files. With --binary it also scans the built .app.

# === Your real claude.ai organization UUID ===
# Paste yours below (literal hex, no angle brackets):
# <your UUID here>

# === Your email addresses ===
# yourname@gmail\.com
# yourname@company\.com

# === Personal bundle ID prefix ===
# (anything in source mentioning your name as bundle ID)
# com\.yourhandle\.

# === Any literal sessionKey you've used ===
# sk-ant-sid01-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# === GitHub or other API tokens (keep these patterns even if you don't
#     think you've ever pasted one — caught early is caught best) ===
# gho_[A-Za-z0-9]{36,}
# ghp_[A-Za-z0-9]{36,}

# === Personal hostnames, IPs, or paths that shouldn't ship ===
# myhost\.local
# /Users/yourname/

# Pro tip: when in doubt, add the pattern. False positives are cheap;
# leaks are forever.
